    <!-- String Naming Conventions

        - Prefixes Overview: Prefixes help categorize strings by their purpose. Some common prefixes include:
            - app_: General application-wide strings.
            - error_: Error messages and notifications.
            - hint_: Hint text for input fields.
            - title_, subtitle_, label_: UI element titles, subtitles, and labels.
            - action_, button_: Text for buttons or actionable elements.
            - dialog_: Text for dialog boxes and pop-ups.

        - Group Related Strings: Group strings related to a specific screen, feature, or functionality.
                                 This facilitates organization and maintenance of the strings resource file.

        Examples:
            - app_name: Application name.
            - error_network: Error message for network-related issues.
            - hint_username: Hint text for the username input field.
            - button_submit: Text for the submit button.

        Group Related Strings (Example: Login Screen):
            - login_title: Title of the login screen.
            - login_username_hint: Hint text for the username input field.
            - login_password_hint: Hint text for the password input field.
            - login_button_submit: Text for the submit button on the login screen.
            - login_error_invalid_credentials: Error message displayed for invalid login credentials.
    -->
